    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1995"/>, n. <citedRange>1</citedRange></bibl>
                        (= <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, pp. <citedRange>320-324</citedRange></bibl>), whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>44.1541, 1</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>001000</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1997"/><citedRange/></bibl>
                    (=<bibl><ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, pp. <citedRange>388-400</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2164</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#maffre2007"/>, n. <citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/><citedRange/></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#marengo2016"/>, p. <citedRange>167</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, pp. <citedRange>382-383</citedRange>, number 109 (text)</bibl>.
                </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo_Korax"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλλō</supplied><unclear>ν</unclear>ι</name> 
                    <rs type="epithet" key="Korax"><name nymRef="#Κόραξ">Ϙ<hi rend="superscript">ό</hi>ρακί</name></rs></persName> <w lemma="ἐγώ">με</w> 
                    <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέ<supplied reason="lost">θε̄κε</supplied></w>	 
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem>Ϙ<hi rend="superscript">ό</hi>ρακί <note>omicron written above rho</note></lem></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Untel</supplied> m'a dédié à <supplied reason="lost">Apollon</supplied> Korax.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied> dedicated me to <supplied reason="lost">Apollo</supplied> Korax.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> mi ha dedicato ad <supplied reason="lost">Apollo</supplied> Korax.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>فلان وفلان أهدوني للمؤله أبوللون كوراكس</p>
         </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>فلان وفلان أهدوني للمؤله [أبوللون] كوراكس</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>According to Callimachus, Hymn II, vv. 65-68, Apollo, in the guise of a crow, 
                    would have guided the founder Battos and his fellows to Cyrene. This archaic graffito shows that Callimachus' information,
                gathered in his homecity, remained vivid.</p>
	<p>As pointed out by <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl>, the lacuna being very large, several names of dedicatns may have been lost at left and the verb might thus be at the plural.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
